-- Westfield to Expand St Lukes, Creating New Zealand's Largest, Herald Says
-- B y   P h o e b e   S e d g m a n
-- 2010-09-21T20:53:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/westfield-to-expand-st-lukes-creating-new-zealand-s-largest-herald-says.html
Westfield Group , the world’s
largest shopping center owner by market value, has been given
permission to double the size of its St Lukes shopping center in
Auckland, making it New Zealand’s biggest, the New Zealand
Herald  reported  today.  Independent planning commissioners recommended the city
council approve the company’s plans to increase floor space to
9.2 hectares (23 acres) from 4.5 hectares, the Auckland-based
newspaper said.  For Related News and Information:
